1.first do npm i 

2.then run index.js file by running command node index.js on the terminal

3.after that check the connectivity of mongodb it should say connected to mongodb and Server running on port 3000

4.then go to postman and hit the first api of creating user or signup by using the route: http://localhost:3000/api/v1/user/ and in body send {"userName":"", "email":"","password":""} in body/raw/json

5.then you can login with the same email and password that you have created before by using the route: http://localhost:3000/api/v1/user/login 

6.next you can get all stored ids by hitting the route http://localhost:3000/api/v1/user/ and this time you have to use the "get" http method and you can also get a edit userName, password, email by using "put and patch" method and by using the email, password 

7.you can also delete the user by hitting http://localhost:3000/api/v1/user/:id (this id you can get from mongodb which is in the name of objectId)







